JUNE 30, 2015, COVERS THE ACCUMULATION OF NET PROPERTY LOSSES ARISING OUT OF ONE OCCURRENCE ON BUSINESS WRITTEN BY THE COMPANY'S CANADIAN BUSINESSES. THE TREATY COVERS ALL PROPERTY WRITTEN BY

THE COMPANY'S CANADIAN BUSINESSES FOR CANADIAN INSUREDS, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, HABITATIONAL PROPERTY, COMMERCIAL PROPERTY, INLAND MARINE, OCEAN MARINE AND AUTO PHYSICAL DAMAGES EXPOSURES,

WITH RESPECT TO RISKS LOCATED WORLDWIDE, WRITTEN FOR CANADIAN INSUREDS. THE TREATY PROVIDES COVERAGE FOR 100% OF LOSS RETAINED IN EXCESS OF C$50 MILLION (US$43 MILLION AT

DECEMBER 31, 2014) UP TO C$900 MILLION (US$775 MILLION AT DECEMBER 31, 2014).

