AND NET WRITTEN PREMIUMS IN 2014 BOTH INCREASED BY 8% OVER THE SAME PERIOD OF 2013, PRIMARILY REFLECTING THE IMPACT OF THE ACQUISITION OF DOMINION. BUSINESS RETENTION RATES IN 2014

REMAINED STRONG AND WERE HIGHER THAN IN 2013. RENEWAL PREMIUM CHANGES REMAINED POSITIVE IN 2014 BUT WERE LOWER THAN IN 2013, PRIMARILY DUE TO A DECLINE IN RENEWAL RATE CHANGES. NEW BUSINESS PREMIUMS

IN 2014 INCREASED OVER 2013.

