THE

DEBT-TO-TOTAL CAPITAL RATIO EXCLUDING NET UNREALIZED GAIN ON INVESTMENTS IS CALCULATED BY DIVIDING (A) DEBT BY (B) TOTAL CAPITALIZATION EXCLUDING NET UNREALIZED GAINS

AND LOSSES ON INVESTMENTS, NET OF TAXES. NET UNREALIZED GAINS AND LOSSES ON INVESTMENTS CAN BE SIGNIFICANTLY IMPACTED BY BOTH INTEREST RATE MOVEMENTS AND OTHER ECONOMIC FACTORS. ACCORDINGLY, IN THE

OPINION OF THE COMPANY'S MANAGEMENT, THE DEBT-TO-TOTAL CAPITAL RATIO CALCULATED ON THIS BASIS PROVIDES ANOTHER USEFUL METRIC FOR INVESTORS TO UNDERSTAND THE COMPANY'S FINANCIAL LEVERAGE POSITION. THE

COMPANY'S RATIO OF DEBT-TO-TOTAL CAPITAL (EXCLUDING AFTER-TAX NET UNREALIZED INVESTMENT GAINS) OF 21.7% AT DECEMBER 31, 2014 WAS WITHIN THE COMPANY'S TARGET RANGE OF 15% TO 25%.

